PREAMBLE

The Light General License (LGL) is designed to promote open-source innovation while protecting the project's sustainability. It allows free use, modification, and distribution for non-commercial purposes, while requiring commercial users to obtain a paid license. This ensures the project remains actively developed and maintained.

This license is inspired by the GNU GPL but adds explicit commercial use restrictions to fund ongoing development.

