4. RESTRICTIONS

4.1. Commercial Use Restriction - Commercial Use (as defined in Section 1) of the Software is prohibited without a Commercial License. The following activities specifically require a Commercial License:

· (a) Selling, reselling, or sublicensing the Software
· (b) Offering the Software as a hosted service (SaaS)
· (c) Integrating the Software into a product or service sold to external customers
· (d) Using the Software to provide paid consulting or professional services
· (e) Distributing the Software as part of a commercial offering

4.2. Internal Business Use - Internal use that does not involve any of the activities in 4.1(a)-(e) is permitted without a Commercial License, subject to the Small Business Exception in Section 6.1.

4.3. Commercial Integration - Integrating the Software into a commercial product or service requires a Commercial License.

4.4. Commercial Services - Offering the Software as a service (SaaS), providing commercial support, or using it for commercial consulting requires a Commercial License.

4.5. No Removal of Notices - You may not remove or alter any copyright, trademark, or license notices in the Software.

